The "DecayingExponentialCurve" is a curve type used to graph exponential decay of a sound.

The curve type is often used in place of the LinearCurve to create exponential decay.

The curve has fields for the min and max input on the X axis.

MinInput - minimum value on the X axis of the graph
MaxOuput - maximum value on the X axis of the graph
HorizontalScaling - decay scale of the graph.
Example:

Below, "default_release_curve" has an input (X axis) range of 1 (0 to 1). The decay scaling is 4.


<Item type="DecayingExponentialCurve" ntOffset="3518">
 <Name>default_release_curve</Name>
 <Flags value="0xAAAAAAA6" />
 <MinInput value="0" />
 <MaxInput value="1" />
 <HorizontalScaling value="4" />
</Item>